  "prayerMeaningTakbirKunutIcin": "Allah is the greatest. (for Kunut prayer)",
  "prayerMeaningElleriBaglama": "Place right hand over left hand, below the navel or on the chest.",
  "prayerMeaningSubhaneke": "O Allah! You are free from all imperfections. I praise You. Your name is blessed. Your majesty is exalted. There is no god but You.",
  "prayerMeaningRukuTesbihi": "Glory be to my Lord, the Great. (3 times)",
  "prayerMeaningRukudanKalkis": "Allah hears those who praise Him.",
  "prayerMeaningRabbenaVeLekelHamd": "Our Lord, praise is Yours.",
  "prayerMeaningSecdeTesbihi": "Glory be to my Lord, the Most High. (3 times)",
  "prayerMeaningCelseDuasi": "O Allah, forgive me, have mercy on me, strengthen me, elevate me, guide me, and grant me well-being.",
  "prayerMeaningAllahummeSalli": "O Allah! Send blessings upon Muhammad and upon the family of Muhammad, as You sent blessings upon Ibrahim and upon the family of Ibrahim. Indeed, You are praiseworthy and glorious.",
  "prayerMeaningAllahummeBarik": "O Allah! Bestow Your blessings upon Muhammad and upon the family of Muhammad, as You bestowed blessings upon Ibrahim and upon the family of Ibrahim. Indeed, You are praiseworthy and glorious.",
  "prayerMeaningRabbenaAtina": "Our Lord! Give us good in this world and good in the Hereafter, and protect us from the punishment of the Fire.",
  "prayerMeaningRabbenağfirli": "Our Lord! Forgive me, my parents, and the believers on the Day when the account is established.",
  "prayerMeaningSelam": "Peace be upon you and the mercy of Allah.",
  "prayerMeaningKunutDuasi": "O Allah! We seek Your help, we seek Your forgiveness, we believe in You, we trust in You, we praise You with goodness, we thank You, we do not disbelieve in You, and we abandon and leave those who disobey You.",
  "prayerMeaningKunutDuasiDevami": "O Allah! You alone we worship, for You alone we pray and prostrate, to You alone we hasten and rush. We hope for Your mercy and fear Your punishment. Indeed, Your punishment will reach the disbelievers.",
  "prayerMeaningTahiyyat": "All greetings, prayers, and good words belong to Allah. O Prophet! Peace be upon you, and the mercy of Allah and His blessings. Peace be upon us and upon the righteous servants of Allah. I bear witness that there is no god but Allah, and I bear witness that Muhammad is His servant and messenger.",
